&lt;p&gt;The list is arranged vertically by default, while the common navigation bar main menu is arranged horizontally, and the secondary drop-down menu is arranged vertically, so we need to float the li element of the main menu so that it can be arranged horizontally. After setting the float, you should remember to clear it. You can use class as a common float and clear-float style, then add the corresponding class to the element that needs to be floated, and add the clear-float class to the parent element of the floated element.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>